The paper deals with a computer vision problem of single image deraining, which involves removing rain from images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep learning model for this problem, which involves feature aggregation and fusion. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also involves some discussion of the spatial structure of rain, which suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
